text: From the outside looking in, the cafe looks rather‚Ä¶intimate. Definitely one of the grandest looking ones in Saigon. I immediately went in to try out their famous Vietnamese coffee because every supermarket here is selling their famed coffee beans. First up, the salted coffee. Not the best tasting one but it would suffice. Second, the banana honey crepe. Not fantastic but it was unique in a sense. Would I come back here again? Not sure. But if I‚Äôm in a group, this would be the perfect setting for a get together for Vietnamese coffee for first timers.

Came here one morning to get a coconut coffee to go and was surprised with the flavour of the coffee. The coconut coffee tastes more like a coconut dessert than necessarily a coffee, yet not in a bad way. There could have been a little more coffee in the drink since it was primarily iced coconut. (Sweetness of the coffee can be altered to liking) Service is kind, speaks good enough English to have a small conversation and they have a good system in place in regards to the orders. I got my coffee to go and it came with everything you would need or want it to come. The coconut shavings were nice, yet something that for me it could have gone without. The cafe had a water/tea station where you could also get your selve serve items too. Overall a good experience and would try this cafe and their coffee again.
A cozy cafe consistent with the look and feel of other outlets. The fruit flavoured drinks can be on the sweeter side however.
More upscale cafe. Higher price than other cafes but nice seating inside and professional staff. 5 service. Coffee was well made: did not try any food

To start off with, the Vietnamese drip coffee here is good, nice, aromatic and strong. The food quality is not too bad too, I tried their banana crepes dessert (Banh Chuoi Mat Ong) which included chopped slices of ginger which I thought was unique. Honey on top was nice. Sadly, the service received from their many staff in store was poor. They had forgotten about my dessert order which I waited for a good 25 minutes after several reminders. The staff seem busy with their own matters as the shop wasn‚Äôt very busy. Atmosphere is nice, with nice music and plenty of seating space. Nice ambience to relax and enjoy.

Have a nice breakfast with a soft music ambience while looking at the hustle and bustle on the street. Tucked at the corner, I enjoyed my breakfast while viewing the busy life of Ho Chi Minh city. They serve a variety of food and drinks to choose from. Service is very helpful but I feel they need to improve because they spill some drinks when serving. The ambience is so relaxing. The price is a bit steep but I don't mind with good food, service and environment.
The worst egg coffee I had in Vietnam‚Ä¶ I doubt if there was egg. I guess you should come here for the ambiance or to buy coffee beens‚Ä¶ Not to Drink‚Ä¶ Not Egg Coffee for Sure..

Nice coffee but extremely expensive. The egg coffee was a unique taste but you can get it cheaper somewhere else. We ordered 2 food but the arrival was way off for both. 1 came first n the other one only arrived 15 mins later.
Beautiful airy interior, air con, good menu choice, go for the pork, rice and fried egg - iced drinks are good here
A well-decorated cafe on a busy street corner with many cars and motorbikes cross-crossing each other. A nice place to see to the world go by. The staff is friendly and attentive.
Great coffee shop with nice view to the streets. Original VNese taste or western taste are served. Lunch meals are also available.
Lovely local coffee shop. Prices are reasonable and the coffee is locally grown so very awesome experience they also sell coffee inside

Nicer than Highland coffee. Came 6 years ago and was trying to seach for this cafe, they did a rebranding. Coffee was inconsistent over the days. Sometimes good sometimes meh.... Food is good. One of the raw cafe that serve hot food and beverages. Most cafe serve only drinks.

I saw the store‚Äôs promotional paper cup on a Vietnam Airlines flight, so I thought to give it a try. The place was quaint, borrowing a concept of East meets Western. Unfortunately, the coffee was underwhelming for my taste, especially since the brand carries the ‚Äúnumber one‚Äù slogan. The beans I chose had a strong cocoa flavor‚Äîwhich I appreciated a lot‚Äîyet it didn‚Äôt spark anything special.

Not so easy to find the traditional drip coffee these days in HCM. Found this cafe that serves a wide variety and their special, Legend coffee. Had problems ordering because it was so confusing with the intensity etc. Im sure the beans are different from the usual even the presentation as well. BUT found it too acidic for my liking. Not much flavours or roast to it. AND it‚Äôs very expensive for a coffee, it was 150000 vnd.

If love vietnamese coffee, you will definitely love this place. It's quite famous and the have a wide variety of coffee from different origin, blends and grounds. Try the premium on, it's a bit expensive but you can truly have an excellent coffee experience. They sell turkish coffee nespresso machine capsules but I don't really recommend it. Focus on vietnamese choices, way better.
Nice relaxing chill place to enjoy a very tasty coffee. Service is top of it's class. Always a good crowd but not over crowded. Not too noisy because of the design.
Delicious coffee, a little bit more expensive than other places but really worth it! Friendly staff and nice interior with AC.
Good drinks, spacious and clean

Legends is a very famous cafe in saigon especially with vietnamese I tried here It is a high end luxurious cafe Coffee was delicious but not a wow Famous saigon bread was tasty but again not a wow But as i said it is kind of high end luxirious cafe You can smoke indoor Second floor has the hole street view It is a busy place And prices are really high compared to vietnam prices. Coffe was around 2.5 dollars.
Love love live the egg coffee! Good place to have your quick work here.

Good coffee. Place is cozy and will make you feel relaxed if you are tired of the busy streets. The moment you open the door the aroma of the coffee will warmly welcome you. I can stay all day here actually. :)
the staff here was very very kind. She tried to help me to buy vietnam traditional sweets:) even if this is not her business. I strongly recommend the coconut coffee set! it tastes niceüòã
Came for the ‚Äúlegendary‚Äù Vietnamese coffee experience, saw a menu of weirdly pretentious names for coffee. Pure percolated rocket fuel is what it is.
Great decor. Comfortable. And good strong coffee.

I ordered a yogurt with fruit. The staff laughed at me I think and then gave me a cup 80% filled with ice and a tiny bit of fruit. No yogurt first time. I paid 70,000 for a cup of ice. Second time I talked to them it was just mixed with a spoon. Third time they used the blender. The final product was okay but it shouldn't have been that difficult. They apologized twice so at least they care.
Nice seating area, good service and good coffee. However the latte (no picture) was too weak. Quite expensive for Vietnamese standards. +free cold herbal tea(?) when you order something.

I'm disappointed with this store for 3 things: 1. Quality: I got Coffee No.4 with ice and milk, but the quality is not as good as in other branch (the best No.4 I've had is at Cong Hoa's branch). I asked for a bit more condensed milk and the staff added too much, and thus the coffee is not that good anymore. 2. The staff was quite inattentive: in other cafes, I find waiters and waitresses going around and serve water/ tea to customers. It would be nicer if Trung Nguyen can do it too (their staff just linger around the store though). At the counter, employees laugh and talk really loud. I was wondering if there's a store supervisor around. 3. The worst thing about this store is the music. Staff plays a Youtube list and there're just soooo many ads. They play all types of instrumental music, unlike in other brands where they play classical music. Sometimes, there's no music for hours, and then dance music (of course with no words as of the protocol). For such a big national chain, I expect them to standardize their playlist (and no ads). Besides, the place is really noisy in the afternoon (since people meet up for business I guess). If you are looking for a nice cafe to sit down and read a book in the afternoon, just don't come here at that time. I sat at a table near the kitchen and the oily food odor lingers around, so I gotta move. In the evening, it's more peaceful when there are not that many people. Definitely not coming back here again.
Classic Coffee Shop and warm surroundings.
smells like smoking and drinks take a long time to come but the ice cream is impressive and tatsy like a cake

A cafe by any other name, slick and well presented, always busy. Pretty good coffee. I was here once with my friends and one morning alone. The morning alone I asked for a Banh Mi but was told they had none, then I asked for some plain bread; also told they had none - was disappointing that all the bread on display was actually fake. To be fair if you like Green tea matcha great; but you are sadly disappointed if you want real dough.
Terrible value. Portions were small. Wouldn‚Äôt even bring food menu to table for you. Lots of items not available. Agree with what one review says, overpriced for air cond.

it‚Äôs tasted the same every time when I back in VN. price maybe almost the same to Starbucks which just a few block away from there, but way much far better than‚Ä¶ delicious, glamorous, fascinating! üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª
Very nice coffee shop in the city center. Some good foods for lunch sound good.

The coffee tastes definitely great. Order your coffee with condensed milk, and make sure it's a nice arabica-robusta blend. It's not just the aroma, the texture of the coffee here is definitely on point too. The vibe is very chill and everyone is just having a relaxing afternoon in the middle of the busy Saigon and hiding from the extreme heat.
Nice place for coffee. Coffee size a bit small. Less than half a cup without the massive amount of ice. WiFi available.

Great coffee spot, which was also convenient to my accommodation (8 min walk). They have the standard variety of hot and cold drinks (coffee, teas). Highly recommend an egg coffee and croissant. Staff are friendly and helpful, also helped me when I accidentally ordered my Grab to a wrong address woops.

Deliciously smooth, chocolatey coffee - had the creative 3, although was encouraged quite well by waitress to order the creative 8, but did not want the increased caffeine late at night. Apparently, 8 is the artificial weasel coffee here, will have to try next time.

I stopped by in the morning and ordered an egg coffee for 86,000 VND but the quality was just mediocre. The coffee didn‚Äôt taste good at all and it took forever for the staff to make. I then stopped by in the evening to buy some gifts for my friends. I was looking at the pre-packaged products on the shelves and one of the employees kept following me around. I did not feel comfortable because I was trying to decide which one to buy and I kept getting interrupted by the employee. I wasn‚Äôt there to steal and you guys have camera so just calm the hell down.
Nice ambience Tried the Signature Legend Coffee & Vietnam Egg Coffee both are good!

I ordered watermelon juice without ice and sugar then they asked me for 68k and the price was 59k in menu. They said special juice. I waited then saw 100ml of juice and the juice was only red color without real taste of watermelon. I thought a special watermelon juice will taste good and they may use a good quality of watermelon. But very worse juice. Sorry but it was a bad experience in 10 years.
Tasty coffee and stylish environment. At the corner of the street, it‚Äôs a good place to relax back. My favorite is No.4 ca phe, very fragrant taste
Coffee was very good! Wifi fast and easy to connect! Would go there again...
Very very noisy. Can't do anything here. Coffee was good but the fruit juice bad. Expensive. Toilet not very clean. Bad experience. Left the place with a headache.
Very good coffee, both traditional and western, brewed with espresso machine. The also serve many other beverages. Nice setting and warm comfortable interiors.
Coffees are great!... not so cheap but worth it. üòâ

Wow! This was by far the worst coffee experience I‚Äôve ever had. We ordered no. 2 and 3 iced with milk to go. After we paid they told us it would take 10-15 min - it took 20 minutes (if they‚Äôd told me this beforehand I would have gone someplace else). The place needs another barista and a second coffee machine. Once we got our coffees they were loaded! with sugar or just tasted super sweet. I tried to explain to the staff that I wanted both without sugar but little to no English hardly improved the situation. We ended up throwing both coffees away and going to another place.
Good place, but bad service. I ordered a coffee and wait for 30 minutes. They brought to me after 3 times reminder. Unfortunately, I have to leave for some businesses, so I cannot taste it.

I am always sceptical of places that advertise with being the number N≈ç 1 of XYZ, but once I had a taste of their traditional vietnamese coffee, oh my, it blew my mind. The only thing I could think of after the coffee was having more it! A truly unique taste.

This is probably one of, if not the first Trung Nguyen coffee in the city. It's nicely decorated on the exterior through to the interior, and has the colonial feel to it. They now do packaged sales, on top of the usual Starbucks-like made to order coffee. It's very premium feeling, and prices follow the feel too. That said, it's a very nice place to just grab a cuppa under the very warm weather.

Chain coffee house born and bred in Vietnam. Good quality coffee. Highly recommend everyone trying the legend coffee, which is the Vietnamese version of kopi luwak, which is civet coffee. My on,y reasoning for giving 4 stars for this location, is one time I visited, it was raining, and the staff would not allow me to sit outside, since they did not want to walk outside. There is an overhang and the seats/table were not getting wet.

We were told this chain were they 'starbucks of Vietnam' perhaps Starbucks have better service.

text: Today my team had to go out to work, so we stopped by Trung Nguyen coffee on Bui Thi Xuan street.  Regarding location, the shop is located at the corner of Cach Mang Thang 8 - Bui Thi Xuan intersection, which is an extremely convenient location for moving. Entering the restaurant, the first thing that impressed me was not the d√©cor, nor the space. Which is... chair. The tables and chairs here are said to be made for us to work and meet deadlines. The table surface is wide so it can fit 4 laptops. The table height is also very suitable, combined with a single-back sofa, extremely soft and comfortable. Even when I'm tired, I lean back and take a nap. Like other Trung Nguyen restaurants, Trung Nguyen Bui Thi Xuan's drink menu is very diverse, from juice to soda. I highly recommend you choose coconut coffee, salt coffee, lemon ginger lemongrass chia seeds. Trung Nguyen also sells many dishes. Today I chose 4 bowls of Gia Lai dry pho. The pho noodles are extremely soft and not dry like regular noodles. The most special is black soy sauce, a delicious sweet soy sauce with a fragrant aroma of soybeans. Soy sauce is also very fragrant when combined with satay. The price of water in Trung Nguyen ranges from 50 - 90k, while food is about 80k per dish. This is a very affordable price, if you compare it to renting a co-working space elsewhere. Come to Trung Nguyen Bui Thi Xuan and experience this wonderful working space!
